<p><font>Bleistein is from Chicago, and thus,
        like Burbank, an American. Chicago at the beginning of
        the century was a prosperous trade-city and Americans
        were in fact a minority group - in 1903 the city's
        population consisted of several racial groups, the
        largest of which were the Germans, with 600.000,
        therewith topping the Americans, who had 350.000
        residents.</font></p>
